  "body": "### Description\r\n\r\n**Steps:**\r\n\r\n1. create an account \r\n2. add some watch only accounts to that account \r\n3. derive some accounts as well\r\n4. remove data folder\r\n5. proceed with onboarding -> I am new to status -> import seed phrase\r\n6. check that no data is recovered \r\n7. restart the app and open wallet\r\n\r\n**Actual result:** data is now recovered\r\n\r\n**Expected result**: the exact expectation is unknown and most likely there is no sense to add extra logic to prevent data from recovering in certain cases (and i am not sure we want to block it). Also, since there is no mechanism that prevents me from `cheating` (like i am saying i am new to status when i am obviously not), there is hard to design what could be done. As suggestion, we can simplify the onboarding to just flows when I have a seed (no matter I used status before or not) and new account creation. And try to fetch data for recovered accounts as a general rule - when there is data returned - then we show it , when there is nothing to fetch - create new profile with the same chat key.\r\n\r\n<img width=\"1512\" alt=\"Screenshot 2023-06-22 at 16 16 28\" src=\"https://github.com/status-im/status-desktop/assets/82375995/317ac2ca-2e32-40da-af85-1eb109ca8364\">\r\n",
